ZH: 水在低温下会凝结成冰。
EN: Water will condense into ice at low temperatures.

ZH: 热气凝结成水珠在窗户上。
EN: The hot air condenses into water droplets on the window.

ZH: 这块巧克力会被加热而凝结。
EN: This piece of chocolate will be heated and solidify.

ZH: 冷空气凝结了云朵，形成了雨水。
EN: The cold air condenses the clouds and forms rainwater.

ZH: 我用热锅把奶水凝结成了乳酪。
EN: I used a hot pot to curdle the milk into cheese.

ZH: 在这种恶劣的天气下，汗水凝结在我的额头上。
EN: In this harsh weather, sweat condenses on my forehead.

ZH: 他们用低温使气体凝结成固体。
EN: They use low temperatures to condense the gas into a solid.

ZH: 通过控制水的温度和湿度，我们能够实现蒸气的凝结。
EN: By controlling the temperature and humidity of water, we can achieve the condensation of vapor.

ZH: 哆啦A梦可以通过手指凝结出各种物品。
EN: Doraemon can condense various items with his fingers.

ZH: 玻璃窗户上的水汽凝结成了奇特的图案。
EN: The water vapor on the glass window condenses into peculiar patterns.

ZH: 在严寒的冬天，呼出的气息凝结成了白色的烟雾。
EN: In the cold winter, the breath condenses into white smoke.

ZH: 在高山上，雾气凝结成水滴，滴水落地。
EN: On the mountains, the mist condenses into water droplets and drips to the ground.

ZH: 在潮湿的环境中，金属容易凝结水珠。
EN: In a humid environment, metal easily condenses water droplets.

ZH: 寒冷的天气使我的眼泪凝结在眼角。
EN: The cold weather causes my tears to crystallize at the corner of my eyes.

ZH: 化学实验室中的实验物质可以通过凝结形成晶体。
EN: The experimental substances in the chemistry lab can form crystals through condensation.

ZH: 玻璃杯中的冰块是水凝结的结果。
EN: The ice cubes in the glass are the result of water condensation.

ZH: 基于蒸发凝结原理，我们制造了一台新型的饮水机。
EN: Based on the principle of evaporation condensation, we have developed a new type of water dispenser.

ZH: 这个新的冷冻器能够通过凝结蒸汽迅速冷却食物。
EN: This new freezer can rapidly cool food by condensing steam.

ZH: 寒冷的气候造成了雨水在地面上凝结成冰。
EN: The cold climate causes rainwater to condense into ice on the ground.

ZH: 这个寒冷的冬天，树叶上的露水凝结成了冰晶。
EN: In this cold winter, the dew on the leaves condenses into ice crystals.
